<h2><a name='sect0' href='#toc0'>Name</a></h2>

<p> num_pes, _num_pes, shmem_n_pes - Returns the number of processing
elements (PEs) used to run the application.
<h2><a name='sect1' href='#toc1'>Synopsis</a></h2>

<p> C or C++: <br>
<pre>#include &lt;mpp/shmem.h&gt;
int _num_pes (void);
int shmem_n_pes (void);
</pre> Fortran: <br>
<pre>include &rsquo;mpp/shmem.fh&rsquo;
I = NUM_PES ()
I = SHMEM_N_PES ()
</pre>
<h2><a name='sect2' href='#toc2'>Description</a></h2>

<p> num_pes() or shmem_n_pes() return the total number of PEs
running in an application.
